{
  "stem": "19111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 261.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "September 6, 1941 was the day when the ghetto was established, and all the Jews had to go.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, the tragedy was so great, all of a sudden we walked out of our-- of our apartment, and we left all our possessions there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Polish neighbors of ours, we had given them away some things rather than leave it there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They stood there crying, a lot of them, bemoaning our fate, and some of them didn't show at all, were hiding in their apartments.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But when we walked out of the gate, we noticed a stream of people walking with bundles on their backs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Mothers holding onto children, and fathers, and everybody, the tears rolling down their-- their eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and there were a lot of Polish, I guess, and Lithuanian hooligans who would actually jump at some of the people and grab their bundles away at a time like that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A lot of them were sickly and could not carry this heavy load, and would drop to the street, and open up, and the contents spilled out.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a scene that has made a very, very great impact on me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I just was walking around with a big pain in my heart.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Couldn't understand it, couldn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I used to turn around with tears in my eyes to my mother and my father.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I say, why?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What have we done wrong?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was only 12 years old, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was very difficult to take it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so, these columns-- after column, after column, from all different districts of the city, they all converged into that area where they designated the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the windows that were facing towards the outside was boarded up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Doors were boarded up.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
